Male genitalia: posterior processi of pygophore large (
Fig. 7
), regularly curved outwards, sligthly angular on the inside, apex rounded with 8–10 small black teeth; inferior processus with two diverging hooks (
Fig. 8
), blackened at the apex. Parameres (
Fig. 6
) digitiform in dorsal view, somewhat dilated in lateral view with hairs at the apex and on the inferior side. Phallus (
Fig. 3
) long, weakly sclerotized, with a pair of small antero-lateral processes, bearing a small lateral expansion in the basic half, ejaculatory reservoir fitted with a strongly sclerotized forked process (
Fig. 5
), ductus seminis (
Fig. 4
) weakly sclerotized, coiled inside the vesica.
